# Baked apples and raspberries with quinoa almond crumble
Got apples, and looking for an awesome recipe? This tart yet sweet, crunchy
yet smooth apple crumble tastes divine! The perfect dessert to end a long
weekend lunch with family and friends. This recipe and many more are available
in The Women’s Weekly Diabetes cookbook available at diabetesshop.com.
Share to Facebook Share to Twitter Email Print
* 2 medium pink lady apples (300g), unpeeled
1 Preheat oven to 160°C/325°F. Grease and line a baking tray with baking
3 Core unpeeled apples about three-quarters of the way down from stem end,
making the hole 4cm (1½ inches) in diameter. Use a small sharp knife to score
around the centre of each apple. Make a small deep cut in the base of each
4 Pack combined berries, rind and sugar firmly into apples; top with crumble
topping. Place apples on tray. Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until apples
 **Crumble topping** - Place ingredients in a small bowl. Rub the mixture
Use your favourite variety of apple; we used pink lady as they have a sweet
